cs.GT, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with a game-theoretic model of network creation, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) category. Additionally, the paper involves the study of computational complexity, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) categories. The use of distance bounds and centrality measures suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. Finally, the focus on non-cooperative behavior and decision-making could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
